 AFTER Two decades, Nigeria is set to participate in Men’s World Team Squash Championship in Washington D, USA from December 15 to 21. The Nigerian team is in Pool B alongside five- time champion, England, Wales and Colombia. Nigeria will start their campaign on day one when they take on Wales on stage one. The President Nigeria Squash Federation, Boye Oyerinde has said the team would put up a good performance in the championship considering the level of the players’ preparation. He said: “It has been a long time since Nigeria participated in the championship so we are hoping to put up a good impression. Having done series of trials and preparations, I am sure our team will put up a good performance at the championship. The tournament is needed for us to get the players exposed,” Oyerinde said. 